                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">In hagiography:
                        Golinduch, the "living martyr," was a Persian princess who became a
                        Christian through the influence of Greek prisoners of war. She was tortured
                        and imprisoned for converting to Christianity, but she was freed by an angel
                        and fled to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/142">Nisibis</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/122">Mabbug</placeName>. She was venerated as a living martyr. Her life was
                        preserved in Georgian.</note>
